Vice President Kamala Harris convened disability rights leaders to emphasize the Biden-Harris Administration's dedication to creating a more inclusive nation for people with disabilities. The event, held during Disability Pride Month and in recognition of the 33rd Anniversary of the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA), highlighted the transformative impact of the ADA and discussed the Administration's efforts to enhance accessibility through investments in transportation infrastructure. These investments include $1.75 billion under the All Stations Accessibility Program (ASAP) to improve accessibility in rail transit systems and $5 billion through the Airport Terminals program to make airports more accessible. The Vice President and senior officials expressed appreciation for disability advocates and reaffirmed the Administration's commitment to upholding disability civil rights laws.